{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/replacing-urls-from-wordpress/","result":{"data":{"wordpressPost":{"id":"04a43835-4c19-59f2-af98-35b1c57879f8","title":"Replace URLs from WordPress","content":"\n<p>WordPress makes it easy to create internal links. However, when <a href=\"https://temptemp3.github.io/hdlesswp/sourcing-gatsby-from-wordpress/\">Sourcing Gatsby from WordPress</a> to GitHub Pages, you instead end up with external links that need to be replaced. Luckily enough, there is a simple way to accomplish this using the gatsby-source-wordpress plugin you already have installed. Here&#8217;s how.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Add the following lines to your gatsby-config.js file under resolve: <code>gatsby-source-wordpress</code>.</p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code> searchAndReplaceContentUrls: {        \n  sourceUrl: \"url_to_wordpress\",        \n  replacementUrl: \"url_to_gh_pages\",\n},</code></pre>\n\n\n\n<p>And deploy</p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>yarn deploy</code></pre>\n\n\n\n<p>Now let&#8217;s see if it works.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>A recent post <a href=\"https://temptemp3.github.io/hdlesswp/create-contact-form/\">creating a contact form</a> has a link to the <a href=\"https://temptemp3.github.io/hdlesswp/contact/\">contact form</a>. If it works, then these links should navigate to a page hosted on GitHub Pages.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you replace url_to_wordpress and url_to_gh_pages in the snippet above, it should world. Mine does.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Sources</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.org/packages/gatsby-source-wordpress/\">https://www.gatsbyjs.org/packages/gatsby-source-wordpress/</a>  </li></ul>\n"},"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Self::starter","subtitle":"Sourcing data from WordPress","author":"Nicholas Shellabarger"}},"allWordpressPost":{"edges":[{"next":{"title":"Add author to copyright","slug":"add-author-to-copyright"},"previous":null,"node":{"id":"0da54eef-dece-5552-9ea5-b5f5dfae5d35"}},{"next":{"title":"Add previous/next links to post template","slug":"create-links-to-next-and-previous-posts"},"previous":{"title":"Order posts by date","slug":"order-post-by-publish-date"},"node":{"id":"a1af1ac9-2241-5319-a3df-4299562c12ff"}},{"next":{"title":"Replace URLs from WordPress","slug":"replacing-urls-from-wordpress"},"previous":{"title":"Add author to copyright","slug":"add-author-to-copyright"},"node":{"id":"6b1533ab-fece-59a8-9626-db196990e4b4"}},{"next":{"title":"Create a contact form","slug":"create-contact-form"},"previous":{"title":"Add previous/next links to post template","slug":"create-links-to-next-and-previous-posts"},"node":{"id":"04a43835-4c19-59f2-af98-35b1c57879f8"}},{"next":{"title":"Deploy to GitHub Pages","slug":"deploy-to-github-pages"},"previous":{"title":"Replace URLs from WordPress","slug":"replacing-urls-from-wordpress"},"node":{"id":"39d8c896-b5e6-5d88-ba71-4c2d8ffde80b"}},{"next":{"title":"Sourcing Gatsby from WordPress","slug":"sourcing-gatsby-from-wordpress"},"previous":{"title":"Create a contact form","slug":"create-contact-form"},"node":{"id":"e9dca70a-05a6-55e4-a652-f04865abd898"}},{"next":{"title":"Hello world!","slug":"hello-world"},"previous":{"title":"Deploy to GitHub Pages","slug":"deploy-to-github-pages"},"node":{"id":"10491e46-3c3f-58fc-a172-03dc3fd35c0f"}},{"next":{"title":"Add analytics","slug":"add-analytics"},"previous":{"title":"Sourcing Gatsby from WordPress","slug":"sourcing-gatsby-from-wordpress"},"node":{"id":"88556ef9-35bc-567d-b592-949a033ba87d"}},{"next":null,"previous":{"title":"Hello world!","slug":"hello-world"},"node":{"id":"cb96676d-2856-57b2-9363-de72c8d30255"}}]}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"id":"04a43835-4c19-59f2-af98-35b1c57879f8"}}}